  fiber: 14 g
  sodium: 1420 mg
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chorizo-egg-and-avocado-breakfast-sandwich-58a7133e171c58315939aac3
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven or toaster oven to 400 degrees. Thinly slice half the @dried chorizo{2%ounce} into rounds. Dice other half. Cut @Yukon gold potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch cubes. Halve, peel, and finely dice @red onion{1}. Halve and pit @avocado{1}. Scoop out flesh from peel with a #spoon{}, then thinly slice.

Add chorizo rounds to a large pan over medium heat. Cook, tossing occasionally, until oil has rendered and rounds are crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from pan with #slotted spoon{} and set aside.

Increase heat under pan to medium-high. Add potatoes and diced chorizo, tossing to coat. Cook until potatoes are crisped, ~{15%minutes}. (TIP: If pan is dry, add a drizzle of oil.) Add onion and cook until softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove mixture from pan and set aside, covering with #foil{} to keep warm.

Split @brioche buns{2} in half and place on a #baking sheet{} cut-side up. Place a handful of @cheddar cheese{½%cup} on each of the bun tops. Toast in oven until cheese is melted and buns are golden brown, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Carefully wipe out pan with a #paper towel{}, then heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in it over medium-high heat. Crack @eggs{2} into a #small bowl{}, checking for any bits of shell. Gently slide into pan. Cook eggs sunny side up to desired doneness, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Layer chorizo and avocado slices on bun bottoms, then top each with an egg and bun top to make sandwiches. Serve with hash and any remaining avocado or chorizo on the side.